<TITLE> Man on trial attempts suicide in Dhaka court </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 10 (bdnews24.com)- A man on trial for arms offences attempted suicide by striking his head against the court wall Tuesday. Ahsan, son of Md Moqbul of Balia village in Sherpur, was subsequently sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital for treatment. Ahsan has been behind bars for eight years without the completion of his case. So far the state has presented only one witness to court. According to case records, Ahsan was arrested in possession of an unlicensed loaded pistol on July 6, 1999. He is accused of taking illegal tolls from the Manda area of the capital. Ahsan told bdnews24.com that he does not want bail now. He demanded that the case against him come to an end. He added that he went to jail when his son was six years old and is now estranged from his wife and other relatives. He claims to have acted out of frustration. An earlier incident of attempted suicide, in the same court in June, saw a man take rat poison. Further cases involving detainees trying to cut their throats have also occurred. Judge AKM Enamul Haq presided over the incident in the courtroom of Dhaka Metropolitan Special Tribunal No. 3. bdnew
